— story's dev notes example doesn't work as written.\n- No code quality concerns. All files clean, typed, under 300 lines.\n\n### 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures — code-review (2026-03-24T18:25:00Z)\n\n- MEDIUM (fixed): `createStateMock()` exported phantom functions `readLocalConfig` and `getProjectRoot` that don't exist in codebase. Split into `createStateMock()` and `createSprintStateMock()`.\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Unused `StoryStatus` type import in `state-builders.ts`.\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Inaccurate JSDoc on `createStateMock()` claiming to match two modules while mixing real and nonexistent functions.\n- LOW (unfixed): `selector.test.ts` wraps shared builders in local helpers rather than using `buildSprintState` directly.\n- LOW (unfixed): No `index.ts` barrel file in `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` — consumers must know `helpers.ts` re-export convention.\n- Architecture concern: Mock factories cannot be used with `vi.mock()` directly due to Vitest hoisting — pattern's value limited until more test files refactored.\n\n### 12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures — verification (2026-03-24T18:30:00Z)\n\n- Proof initially failed validation: missing `**Tier:** unit-testable` header required by `validateProofQuality()` to skip black-box enforcement checks\n- Fixed by adding tier header to proof document\n- All 10 ACs passed with direct CLI verification — no Docker needed\n\n### 13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types — create-story (2026-03-24T18:32:00Z)\n\n- Expanded from 2 ACs to 10 ACs based on architecture spec and codebase conventions\n- All ACs tagged cli-verifiable — types-only story with no external system interactions\n- Risk: AC10 (type-level tests) may be shallow — testing type importability is straightforward but verifying discriminated union completeness requires runtime type guards beyond pure type definitions\n\n### 13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types — code-review (2026-03-24T19:40:00Z)\n\n- LOW: `AgentProcess.on('error')` overload not in AC4 spec — kept as u