{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RxtXpZWnYkR4n6wqYyhTyt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 14-1: Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline (Step 8b) + Persistent epic-TD\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer running harness-run,\n     8→I want retro action items to auto-create stories under epic-TD,\n     9→So that tech debt gets tracked and prioritized automatically.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a retro file with `### Fix Now` items, when Step 8b runs, then new `TD-N-slug: backlog` entries appear in sprint-state.json under epic-TD <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `epic-TD` doesn't exist, when Step 8b creates the first TD story, then `epic-TD` is created with `status: in-progress` (never transitions to `done`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given a duplicate action item (80%+ word overlap with existing TD story), when Step 8b processes it, then it's skipped with `[INFO]` message <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→## Technical Notes\n    18→\n    19→**Decision 6 (Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline).** Three mechanisms: persistent epic-TD, retro auto-creates stories, tech debt gate. This story covers the first two.\n    20→\n    21→### Step 8b Implementation\n    22→\n    23→After the session retro subagent writes the retro markdown file, harness-run parses the `## 6. Action Items` section.\n    24→\n    25→The retro parser already exists at `src/lib/retro-parser.ts`. Extend it to:\n    26→1. Parse `### Fix Now` and `### Fix Soon` items from the action items section\n    27→2. For each item, generate a story key: `TD-{N}-{slug}` where N is auto-incremented\n    28→3. Check for duplicates: normalize both the new item text and existing TD story titles (lowercase, remove punctuation, split into words), compute word overlap percentage. If >= 80%, skip with `[INFO] Skipping duplicate: \"{item}\" matches existing \"{existing}\"`\n    29→4. Create new story entries in `sprint-state.json` under `epics['epic-TD'].stories`\n    30→5. `### Backlog` items append to `tech-debt-backlog.md` for tracking only (not active stories)\n    31→\n    32→### Persistent epic-TD\n    33→\n    34→In `src/modules/sprint/state.ts`, add special handling:\n    35→- `epic-TD` is auto-created when the first TD story is added\n    36→- `epic-TD.status` is always `'in-progress'` -- the epic completion logic in Step 5 must skip it\n    37→- New TD stories append to it from any source (retro, audit, manual)\n    38→\n    39→Modify the epic completion check in `src/modules/sprint/selector.ts` or wherever epics are marked `done` to exclude `epic-TD`.\n    40→\n    41→### Retro file location\n    42→\n    43→Retro files are written to `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-YYYY-MM-DD.md`. The parser reads the most recent one.\n    44→\n    45→## Files to Change\n    46→\n    47→- `src/lib/retro-parser.ts` — Extend to parse `### Fix Now` / `### Fix Soon` action items, generate TD story keys, deduplication logic\n    48→- `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` — Add `createTdStory()`, `ensureEpicTd()` functions. Prevent epic-TD from transitioning to `done`\n    49→- `src/modules/sprint/selector.ts` — Skip epic-TD in epic completion checks\n    50→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Add Step 8b: after retro, call retro parser and create TD stories\n    51→- `src/lib/retro-parser.ts` or new `src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts` — Deduplication logic with 80% word overlap detection\n    52→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01E3VQC87sxVSnH1aNNzcpTd","session_id":"d308c3c3-ed4a-4164-bef5-0fade3bd8d38","uuid":"4c90fbc5-a4d2-4c02-84ae-8827adcd53e2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:42:26.913Z"}
