{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E3VQC87sxVSnH1aNNzcpTd","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story 14-1 has been expanded and set to `ready-for-dev`.\n\n**What was done:**\n\n- Expanded the existing 3 ACs to 10, covering: Fix Now/Fix Soon/Backlog parsing, epic-TD auto-creation and incremental updates, deduplication with 80% word overlap, YAML generation override, build/test regression checks, and 300-line limit compliance.\n- Added verification tags to all ACs: all 10 tagged `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` since they can all be verified by running CLI commands, unit tests, or inspecting file output in a subprocess.\n- Added 11 tasks with subtasks, mapping each to specific ACs.\n- Added comprehensive Dev Notes with: architecture compliance, implementation guidance for the retro section parser, TD story key generation, deduplication algorithm, epic-TD state handling, testing guidance, previous story intelligence, and code observations.\n- Set status from `backlog` to `ready-for-dev`.\n\n**File modified:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td.md`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- `state.ts` is already 525 lines (over the 300-line limit). New TD management functions cannot go there without worsening the violation. Story notes recommend `src/lib/retro-to-sprint.ts` as the new orchestrator file instead.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- None.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- `parseStoryKey()` returns `[Infinity, Infinity]` for `TD-` prefixed keys. TD stories will not group correctly in YAML output unless `parseStoryKey()` or `generateSprintStatusYaml()` is patched. This is called out in Dev Notes but adds scope.\n- The retro file `## 6. Action Items` section uses inconsistent header formats across sessions (e.g., `###` vs `####`, varying parenthetical suffixes like `(Before Next Session)` vs `(Next Sprint / Next Session)` vs `(Next Sprint)`). The parser must be robust to these variations.\n- `state.ts` being over 300 lines means modifying it for the epic-TD YAML override technically violates the project's own NFR5. Minimal change (2-3 lines) is defensible but worth noting.\n\n**Observations:**\n- All 10 ACs are cli-verifiable. None require integration testing with external systems, workflow orchestration, or user sessions — the retro content is just a string input and sprint-state is just a JSON file.\n- The existing `parseRetroActionItems()` parses a completely different format (table-based `| # | Action | Status | Notes |`) from what this story needs (subsection-based `### Fix Now` / bullet lists). These are complementary, not overlapping."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0a1c942800ee4c1c (use SendMessage with to: 'a0a1c942800ee4c1c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 41310\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 146522</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d308c3c3-ed4a-4164-bef5-0fade3bd8d38","uuid":"aac07261-9eef-48e4-8525-9cbc07f512a9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:44:49.074Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` based on whether the AC can be verified by running CLI commands in a subprocess. ACs referencing workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, or external system interactions should be tagged as integration-required. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nCONTEXT: The story file already exists at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td.md with 3 ACs and technical notes. It needs to be expanded/v