itions minimal (~18 lines for `getEpicGroupKey` and the epic-TD override in YAML generation). The pre-existing 525-line bloat is not addressed by this story.\n- **Backlog file append is I/O in `processRetroActionItems()`:** The `projectRoot` parameter is optional and file writing is skipped when absent — this makes the function testable without mocking fs, but means callers must remember to pass it when they want file output. This is a reasonable trade-off for testability.\n- **No integration with the actual harness-run pipeline yet:** This story creates the library functions; wiring them into the actual retro processing step (step 8b of the run loop) is not part of this story's scope."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a142b834f92f0413d (use SendMessage with to: 'a142b834f92f0413d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61791\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 256969</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d308c3c3-ed4a-4164-bef5-0fade3bd8d38","uuid":"11c64d25-550d-4457-92ee-cff49c1848d6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:50:53.815Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a142b834f92f0413d","content":